Names of 398 victims, who boarded the ill-fated Abuja-Kaduna train, have emerged. Recalled that on Monday night, some gunmen suspected to be terrorists bombed the Abuja-Kaduna train between Katari and Rigina axis, leaving hundreds of passengers dead in the attack. DAILY POST gathered that during the attack, many passengers were said to have been initially kidnapped, including Zamfara State former deputy Governor, Mallam Ibrahim Wakkala Liman. Others were shot dead and an unascertained number of the passengers also sustained various degrees of injury as a result of gunshots. Rotimi Amaechi, the Minister of Transportation, disclosed that no fewer than eight persons were killed during the terroristsâ€™ attack. He spoke on Tuesday while inspecting the site of the incident. Amaechi said 25 people have been hospitalized due to the attack. The names of 398 passengers, who were on board the bombed train, have now surfaced. Meanwhile, the Minister disclosed that some of the passengers were still missing. See attached:        